WEBVTT

00:05.260 --> 00:10.700
THE GOSPEL OF SAINT LUKE The Authorized Version, commonly known as

00:10.700 --> 00:15.900
the King James Version, chapters 15 and 16.

00:30.760 --> 00:35.340
This is Father Zeile of Detroit, December 2008.

00:36.820 --> 00:41.180
THE GOSPEL ACCORDING TO SAINT LUKE, CHAPTERS 15 AND 16.

00:43.380 --> 00:47.400
Then drew near unto him all the publicans and sinners for to hear him.

00:47.960 --> 00:52.740
And the Pharisees and scribes murmured, saying, This man receiveth sinners,

00:53.000 --> 00:57.440
and eateth with them. And he spake this parable unto them, saying,

00:58.640 --> 01:02.800
What man of you, having an hundred sheep, if he lose one of them,

01:02.800 --> 01:08.180
doth not leave the ninety and nine in the wilderness, and go after that which is lost,

01:08.380 --> 01:14.280
until he find it? And when he hath found it, he layeth it on his shoulders, rejoicing.

01:15.200 --> 01:18.720
And when he cometh home, he calleth together his friends and neighbors,

01:18.880 --> 01:24.080
saying unto them, Rejoice with me, for I have found my sheep which was lost.

01:24.840 --> 01:31.020
I say unto you, that likewise joy shall be in heaven over one sinner that repenteth,

01:31.020 --> 01:35.840
more than over ninety and nine just persons which need no repentance.

01:37.940 --> 01:43.060
Either what woman, having ten pieces of silver, if she lose one piece,

01:43.480 --> 01:48.960
doth not light a candle, and sweep the house, and seek diligently till she find it.

01:49.200 --> 01:53.160
And when she hath found it, she calleth her friends and her neighbors together,

01:53.300 --> 01:57.760
saying, Rejoice with me, for I have found the piece which I had lost.

01:59.040 --> 02:05.580
Likewise I say unto you, there is joy in the presence of the angels of God over one sinner

02:05.580 --> 02:14.900
that repenteth. And he said, A certain man had two sons, and the younger of them said to his father,

02:15.720 --> 02:23.600
Father, give me the portion of goods that falleth to me. And he divided unto him his living.

02:25.080 --> 02:31.780
And not many days after the younger son gathered all together, and took his journey into a far

02:31.780 --> 02:38.840
country, and there wasted his substance with riotous living. And when he had spent all,

02:39.560 --> 02:46.320
there arose a mighty famine in that land, and he began to be in want. And he went and joined

02:46.320 --> 02:53.580
himself to a citizen of that country, and he sent him into his fields to feed swine. And he would

02:53.580 --> 02:59.800
have filled his belly with the husks that the swine did eat, and no man gave unto him.

03:01.220 --> 03:07.540
And when he came to himself, he said, How many hired servants of my fathers have

03:07.540 --> 03:14.700
bred enough and to spare, and I perish with hunger. I will arise and go to my father,

03:15.160 --> 03:21.100
and will say unto him, Father, I have sinned against heaven and before thee,

03:21.100 --> 03:27.600
and am no more worthy to be called thy son. Make me as one of thy hired servants.

03:28.660 --> 03:34.460
And he arose and came to his father. But when he was yet a great way off,

03:34.880 --> 03:40.740
his father saw him, and had compassion, and ran, and fell on his neck, and kissed him.

03:41.460 --> 03:48.140
And the son said unto him, Father, I have sinned against heaven, and in thy sight,

03:48.140 --> 03:54.680
and am no more worthy to be called thy son. But the father said to his servants,

03:55.640 --> 04:02.000
Bring forth the best robe, and put it on him, and put a ring on his hand, and shoes on his feet,

04:02.640 --> 04:09.320
and bring hither the fatted calf, and kill it, and let us eat, and be merry. For this my son was dead,

04:09.480 --> 04:15.820
and is alive again. He was lost, and is found. And they began to be merry.

04:16.520 --> 04:22.780
Now his elder brother was in the field, and as he came and drew nigh to the house,

04:23.340 --> 04:29.520
he heard music and dancing. And he called one of the servants, and asked what these things meant.

04:30.540 --> 04:36.340
And he said unto him, Thy brother is come, and thy father hath killed the fatted calf,

04:36.800 --> 04:45.100
because he hath received him safe and sound. And he was angry, and would not go in. Therefore

04:45.100 --> 04:51.760
came his father out, and entreated him. And he answering said to his father, Lo,

04:51.940 --> 04:57.720
these many years do I serve thee, neither transgressed I at any time thy commandment,

04:58.020 --> 05:04.940
and yet thou never gavest me a kid, that I might make merry with my friends. But as soon as this

05:04.940 --> 05:10.520
thy son was come, which hath devoured thy living with harlots, thou hast killed for him the fatted

05:10.520 --> 05:20.940
calf. And he said unto him, Son, thou art ever with me, and all that I have is thine. It was

05:20.940 --> 05:27.400
meet that we should make merry and be glad. For this thy brother was dead, and is alive again,

05:27.860 --> 05:33.860
and was lost, and is found. CHAPTER 16

05:33.860 --> 05:41.480
And he said also unto his disciples, There was a certain rich man, which had a steward. And the

05:41.480 --> 05:47.380
same was accused unto him, that he had wasted his goods. And he called him, and said unto him,

05:48.040 --> 05:53.900
How is it that I hear this of thee? Give an account of thy stewardship, or thou mayest be

05:53.900 --> 06:00.740
no longer steward. Then the steward said within himself, What shall I do? For my Lord taketh

06:00.740 --> 06:08.360
away from me the stewardship. I cannot dig, to beg I am ashamed. I am resolved what to do,

06:08.620 --> 06:14.720
that when I am put out of the stewardship, they may receive me into their houses. So he called

06:14.720 --> 06:20.860
every one of his Lord's debtors unto him, and said unto the first, How much owest thou unto my

06:20.860 --> 06:28.860
Lord? And he said, On hundred measures of oil. And he said unto him, Take thy bill, and sit down

06:28.860 --> 06:36.280
quickly, and write fifty. Then said he to another, And how much owest thou? And he said,

06:36.600 --> 06:42.580
And hundred measures of wheat. And he said unto him, Take thy bill, and write four score.

06:43.940 --> 06:49.880
And the Lord commended the unjust steward, because he had done wisely, for the children

06:49.880 --> 06:56.200
of this world are in their generation wiser than the children of light. And I say unto you,

06:56.200 --> 07:01.800
Make to yourselves friends of the mammon of unrighteousness, that when ye fail,

07:02.300 --> 07:09.200
they may receive you into everlasting habitations. He that is faithful in that which is least,

07:09.620 --> 07:18.820
is faithful also in much. And he that is unjust in the least, is unjust also in much. If therefore

07:18.820 --> 07:25.060
ye have not been faithful in the unrighteous mammon, who will commit to your trust the true

07:25.060 --> 07:31.360
riches? And if ye have not been faithful in that which is another man's, who shall give you that

07:31.360 --> 07:38.280
which is your own? No servant can serve two masters, for either he will hate the one and

07:38.280 --> 07:45.200
love the other, or else he will hold to the one and despise the other. Ye cannot serve God and

07:45.200 --> 07:52.820
mammon. And the Pharisees also who were covetous heard all these things, and they derided him.

07:52.820 --> 08:00.280
And he said unto them, Ye are they which justify yourselves before men, but God knoweth your

08:00.280 --> 08:06.380
hearts. For that which is highly esteemed among men, is abomination in the sight of God.

08:07.260 --> 08:13.920
The law and the prophets were until John. Since that time the kingdom of God is preached,

08:14.180 --> 08:19.700
and every man presseth into it. And it is easier for heaven and earth to pass,

08:19.700 --> 08:26.340
than one tittle of the law to fail. Whosoever putteth away his wife, and marryeth another,

08:26.780 --> 08:31.260
committeth adultery. And whosoever marryeth her that is put away from her husband,

08:31.560 --> 08:38.120
committeth adultery. There was a certain rich man, which was clothed in purple and fine linen,

08:38.400 --> 08:44.860
and fared sumptuously every day. And there was a certain beggar named Lazarus, which was laid at

08:44.860 --> 08:51.040
his gate full of sores, and desiring to be fed with the crumbs which fell from the rich man's

08:51.040 --> 08:59.100
table. Moreover the dogs came, and licked his sores. And it came to pass, that the beggar died,

08:59.280 --> 09:06.320
and was carried by the angels into Abraham's bosom. The rich man also died, and was buried,

09:06.800 --> 09:13.940
and in hell he lifted up his eyes, being in torment, and seeth Abraham afar off and Lazarus

09:13.940 --> 09:21.400
in his bosom. And he cried, and said, Father Abraham, have mercy on me, and send Lazarus that he may

09:21.400 --> 09:27.060
dip the tip of his finger in water, and cool my tongue, for I am tormented in this flame.

09:28.620 --> 09:35.360
But Abraham said, Son, remember that thou in thy lifetime receivest thy good things,

09:35.660 --> 09:41.700
and likewise Lazarus' evil things. But now he is comforted, and thou are tormented.

09:42.560 --> 09:50.660
And beside all this, between us and you there is a great gulf fixed, so that they which would pass

09:50.660 --> 09:58.340
from hence to you cannot, neither can they pass to us that would come from thence. Then he said,

09:58.500 --> 10:04.560
I pray thee therefore, Father, that thou wouldest send him to my father's house, for I have five

10:04.560 --> 10:10.260
brethren, that he may testify unto them, lest they also come into this place of torment.

10:11.340 --> 10:18.900
Abraham saith unto him, They have Moses and the prophets, let them hear them. And he said,

10:19.160 --> 10:24.640
Nay, Father Abraham, but if one went unto them from the dead, they will repent.

10:25.740 --> 10:30.960
And he said unto him, If they hear not Moses and the prophets,

10:31.660 --> 10:35.620
neither will they be persuaded, though one rose from the dead.

10:37.840 --> 10:42.280
End of chapter 16, the Gospel according to Saint Luke,

10:43.480 --> 10:49.180
and the authorized version known as the King James Version, chapter 16 and 17.

